item.title: Removed
item.dc:creator: @iamlies iamlies
item.description:
@iamlies wrote:

Here is some good advice:
You need to change the tutorial because I had the same problem with the invisible nex. Where you place the .dat in the “Frames” you should say you need to rename it. Also to make nex use all three attack styles use this code under:

public void loadSpell(int i) { located in NPChandler

case 6032: //npc id if (goodDistance(npcs[i].absX, npcs[i].absY, Server.playerHandler.players[npcs[i].killerId].absX, Server.playerHandler.players[npcs[i].killerId].absY, 2)) r3 = Misc.random(2); else r3 = Misc.random(1); if (r3 == 0) { npcs[i].attackType = 2; npcs[i].gfx100(000); //change the zeros to your own gfx npcs[i].projectileId = 0000; //change the zeros to your own id } else if (r3 == 1) { npcs[i].attackType = 1; npcs[i].projectileId = 000; //change the zeros to your own id } else if (r3 == 2) { npcs[i].attackType = 0; npcs[i].projectileId = -1; } break;
Thanks
